The upper canine and premolars of 

N. lynasi

are represented by RAM 9668 (C and P4, with alveoli of P2–3), RAM 6931 (P3), and RAM 9669 (P4). In RAM 9668 (
fig. 5C
), a single-rooted tooth is positioned adjacent to the anterior alveolus of P2, indicating the lack of a diastema between the teeth. This rarely preserved tooth has been identified as the canine in plesiadapids (
Gingerich, 1976
; 
Boyer, 2009
